The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Mhambrey against hiring foreign players

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Bengal coach Paras Mhambrey, who took charge of the squad for the 2006-07 season on Monday, doesnt feel hiring foreign players in domestic tournaments is a good idea. 

If we hire players from abroad to do duty for the state team, then what is the necessity of preparing under-22 or under-19 sides? Mhambrey posed. 

He, however, feels that it is absolutely necessary for players to practise on turfs. I will talk to CAB regarding this and try to arrange something quickly, Mhambrey said. 

The Bengal coach said Sourav Gangulys presence amongst the youngsters during the Moin-ud-Dowlah Gold Cup was of lot oif help. 

His presence inspires the youngsters like anything and I would like him to play as many matches as possible for Bengal in the Ranji Trophy, Mhambrey said. He also praised Sourav for introducing methods like kick-boxing for enhancing the fitness level. 

The coach appeared bothered about Bengals tough fixture in Ranji Trophy. 




